1
00:01:55,720 --> 00:01:57,320
My first job after graduating from college

2
00:01:57,320 --> 00:01:58,440
was at a TV station.

3
00:02:05,480 --> 00:02:06,680
I was young back then

4
00:02:07,840 --> 00:02:09,169
and had endless energy.

5
00:02:11,039 --> 00:02:12,040
Every day,

6
00:02:12,280 --> 00:02:13,480
I looked for topics,

7
00:02:13,480 --> 00:02:14,480
chased leads,

8
00:02:15,640 --> 00:02:16,970
and wrote news stories.

9
00:02:18,960 --> 00:02:20,440
It took me five years

10
00:02:21,160 --> 00:02:22,760
to go from an intern reporter

11
00:02:23,600 --> 00:02:25,120
to a show host.

12
00:02:32,840 --> 00:02:35,560
While I was doing a wilderness survival show,

13
00:02:36,840 --> 00:02:38,720
I accidentally broke my ribs.

14
00:02:40,320 --> 00:02:41,240
At that time,

15
00:02:42,000 --> 00:02:43,240
I just used tape

16
00:02:43,240 --> 00:02:45,040
to simply bind the injury,

17
00:02:46,400 --> 00:02:48,860
and continued to finish recording the show.

18
00:02:50,200 --> 00:02:52,200
Back then, every word I spoke

19
00:02:52,680 --> 00:02:54,000
was a piercing pain.

20
00:02:56,360 --> 00:02:58,760
But when the show was broadcast,

21
00:02:58,880 --> 00:03:00,920
surprisingly no one could tell.

22
00:03:01,240 --> 00:03:02,520
From that moment on,

23
00:03:04,120 --> 00:03:06,640
my colleagues all called me a workaholic.

24
00:03:16,320 --> 00:03:18,579
Work used to be your happiness and pride.

25
00:03:19,880 --> 00:03:21,120
Since when

26
00:03:21,120 --> 00:03:24,120
did it become the source of your anxiety and pressure?

27
00:03:27,840 --> 00:03:30,040
When I first saw you at the fencing club,

28
00:03:30,600 --> 00:03:32,200
I felt you were like a taut string

29
00:03:32,200 --> 00:03:33,860
that could snap at any moment.

30
00:03:37,440 --> 00:03:38,280
Ten years ago,

31
00:03:39,240 --> 00:03:41,570
I saw the potential in the media industry,

32
00:03:43,040 --> 00:03:44,370
so I left the TV station.

33
00:03:46,040 --> 00:03:48,570
Later, I founded One Thousand and One Nights.

34
00:03:53,160 --> 00:03:54,160
I wanted to create

35
00:03:54,160 --> 00:03:56,360
my ideal media empire.

36
00:03:58,200 --> 00:03:59,160
So,

37
00:03:59,440 --> 00:04:01,280
I kept my nerves tense every day.

38
00:04:03,320 --> 00:04:05,040
Everything I held in my hands,

39
00:04:05,440 --> 00:04:06,640
I refused to let go of.

40
00:04:07,480 --> 00:04:10,280
But when I finally reached the top of the mountain,

41
00:04:10,800 --> 00:04:11,840
I found that

42
00:04:12,600 --> 00:04:14,080
I had nothing in my hands.

43
00:04:15,960 --> 00:04:16,820
I couldn't even

44
00:04:17,880 --> 00:04:19,880
see myself clearly anymore.

45
00:04:22,960 --> 00:04:23,480
So,

46
00:04:24,240 --> 00:04:25,560
in your subconscious,

47
00:04:26,240 --> 00:04:28,170
are you disappointed in yourself,

48
00:04:28,440 --> 00:04:30,370
or disillusioned with this ideal?

49
00:04:31,640 --> 00:04:32,400
I don't know.

50
00:04:35,520 --> 00:04:37,280
I only know that I can't stop.

51
00:04:40,000 --> 00:04:42,560
Ai Wei is no longer just a person.

52
00:04:43,240 --> 00:04:44,680
It is a team,

53
00:04:46,240 --> 00:04:47,320
a company,

54
00:04:48,520 --> 00:04:50,780
a brand valued at over a hundred million.

55
00:04:53,080 --> 00:04:55,800
The media industry evolves so fast.

56
00:04:56,960 --> 00:04:58,400
If you are not careful for a moment,

57
00:04:58,400 --> 00:05:00,460
you will disappear into the big data.

58
00:05:02,080 --> 00:05:03,200
But I am Ai Wei.

59
00:05:04,480 --> 00:05:06,120
I must stand at the top.

60
00:05:08,000 --> 00:05:09,800
I must be flawless.

61
00:05:13,720 --> 00:05:14,840
You've seen it too,

62
00:05:15,920 --> 00:05:17,520
how many malicious people

63
00:05:18,080 --> 00:05:20,340
are waiting to see me make a fool of myself

64
00:05:21,040 --> 00:05:23,440
and waiting for me to fall off the mountain.

65
00:05:25,880 --> 00:05:26,720
Later,

66
00:05:27,160 --> 00:05:29,160
I couldn't sleep night after night.

67
00:05:31,840 --> 00:05:34,040
Every time my anxiety attacked,

68
00:05:34,880 --> 00:05:36,320
even the slightest noise

69
00:05:38,159 --> 00:05:40,720
felt like a tsunami

70
00:05:40,800 --> 00:05:42,400
crushing over me.

71
00:05:45,440 --> 00:05:46,280
And then?

72
00:05:51,680 --> 00:05:53,159
Actually, in the past,

73
00:05:53,520 --> 00:05:54,760
I used to look down on

74
00:05:54,760 --> 00:05:56,420
those who committed suicide.

75
00:05:56,760 --> 00:05:59,120
I thought they were too cowardly.

76
00:06:01,440 --> 00:06:03,400
When I couldn't sleep at night

77
00:06:04,400 --> 00:06:06,840
and looked down from my balcony,

78
00:06:07,680 --> 00:06:09,280
I suddenly understood them.

79
00:06:11,160 --> 00:06:12,120
It turns out...

80
00:06:12,800 --> 00:06:15,080
Death doesn't solve any problems.

81
00:06:15,560 --> 00:06:16,520
But at least

82
00:06:17,000 --> 00:06:19,460
you don't have to face any problems anymore.

83
00:06:21,320 --> 00:06:23,280
Then how did you drop the idea?

84
00:06:27,160 --> 00:06:28,600
Because I'm Aiwei.

85
00:06:30,720 --> 00:06:31,850
Ridiculous, right?

86
00:06:38,200 --> 00:06:39,640
If I died,

87
00:06:40,520 --> 00:06:41,320
there would be

88
00:06:41,600 --> 00:06:43,320
media like flies

89
00:06:43,840 --> 00:06:45,240
swarming over

90
00:06:46,440 --> 00:06:48,240
to make a fuss about my death.

91
00:06:49,200 --> 00:06:50,530
I wouldn't accept that.

92
00:06:53,080 --> 00:06:53,960
Aiwei,

93
00:06:56,640 --> 00:06:58,040
whether dead

94
00:06:58,840 --> 00:06:59,800
or alive,

95
00:07:00,960 --> 00:07:01,920
is never free.

96
00:07:06,920 --> 00:07:08,720
I spent so much time

97
00:07:10,600 --> 00:07:12,680
and gave my all for this name.

98
00:07:16,000 --> 00:07:17,440
But I never expected

99
00:07:18,720 --> 00:07:19,680
that in the end,

100
00:07:21,520 --> 00:07:23,640
it would become a joke,

101
00:07:26,600 --> 00:07:27,720
a bubble.

102
00:07:32,320 --> 00:07:33,040
It's okay.

103
00:07:35,240 --> 00:07:37,170
It doesn't matter if it's a bubble.

104
00:07:38,480 --> 00:07:38,960
Aiwei,

105
00:07:40,240 --> 00:07:41,080
whether good

106
00:07:41,360 --> 00:07:41,800
or bad,

107
00:07:42,040 --> 00:07:43,240
it's all a part of you.

108
00:07:43,920 --> 00:07:45,380
As long as you accept this,

109
00:07:46,520 --> 00:07:47,560
you are free.

110
00:08:43,240 --> 00:08:43,760
Lu.

111
00:08:44,360 --> 00:08:45,680
I just got some new tea.

112
00:08:46,760 --> 00:08:47,520
This is the only one.

113
00:08:47,520 --> 00:08:48,980
I'm giving it to you to try.

114
00:08:49,280 --> 00:08:49,920
Thank you, Mr. Li.

115
00:08:49,920 --> 00:08:51,580
You were still thinking of me.

116
00:08:52,160 --> 00:08:52,760
How are you doing?

117
00:08:52,760 --> 00:08:54,290
Have you been tired lately?

118
00:08:57,000 --> 00:08:58,160
In this position,

119
00:08:58,720 --> 00:09:00,280
it's only right to do more.

120
00:09:02,760 --> 00:09:03,240
Yes.

121
00:09:03,240 --> 00:09:04,500
It must be hard for you.

122
00:09:05,360 --> 00:09:05,960
Well,

123
00:09:06,160 --> 00:09:07,240
after Ai Wei left,

124
00:09:07,840 --> 00:09:08,770
you still have to

125
00:09:09,120 --> 00:09:09,760
manage

126
00:09:09,960 --> 00:09:11,400
Liguang and 1001 Nights.

127
00:09:13,000 --> 00:09:15,130
The pressure and burden are not small.

128
00:09:16,080 --> 00:09:18,200
Did the data drop a bit last month?

129
00:09:19,040 --> 00:09:19,440
Mr. Li,

130
00:09:19,800 --> 00:09:21,400
I just took over 1001 Nights.

131
00:09:22,160 --> 00:09:22,840
I assure you,

132
00:09:22,840 --> 00:09:25,700
next month's data will definitely not be like this.

133
00:09:26,200 --> 00:09:26,800
I know.

134
00:09:26,800 --> 00:09:27,440
I know.

135
00:09:28,520 --> 00:09:29,720
Don't misunderstand.

136
00:09:29,720 --> 00:09:30,480
I didn't have any

137
00:09:30,480 --> 00:09:32,040
intention of blaming you.

138
00:09:33,440 --> 00:09:34,440
I just want to say,

139
00:09:35,280 --> 00:09:35,920
well,

140
00:09:36,320 --> 00:09:37,840
a single thread does not make a string,

141
00:09:37,840 --> 00:09:40,040
and a single tree does not make a forest.

142
00:09:41,000 --> 00:09:42,000
No matter how excellent

143
00:09:42,000 --> 00:09:42,920
an organization

144
00:09:42,920 --> 00:09:43,780
or a company is,

145
00:09:44,840 --> 00:09:46,200
if it wants to become stronger

146
00:09:46,200 --> 00:09:47,760
and invincible,

147
00:09:48,360 --> 00:09:49,600
it needs a continuous

148
00:09:49,600 --> 00:09:51,120
infusion of fresh blood.

149
00:09:52,040 --> 00:09:52,970
Don't you agree?

150
00:09:56,360 --> 00:09:57,560
You are right, Mr. Li.

151
00:09:59,240 --> 00:10:00,040
You are right.

152
00:10:02,600 --> 00:10:02,880
Lu.

153
00:10:02,880 --> 00:10:04,280
This tea is exceptionally good.

154
00:10:04,280 --> 00:10:05,340
Don't give it away.

155
00:10:05,440 --> 00:10:06,500
Drink it yourself.

156
00:10:09,080 --> 00:10:09,520
Come.

157
00:10:22,320 --> 00:10:24,040
I asked Mr. Li's secretary.

158
00:10:25,400 --> 00:10:26,240
I heard

159
00:10:26,920 --> 00:10:30,180
Mr. Li has been contacting Huican's operations director.

160
00:10:31,080 --> 00:10:31,600
And

161
00:10:32,400 --> 00:10:33,600
he wants to poach him.

162
00:10:42,200 --> 00:10:43,000
Mr. Lu,

163
00:10:43,720 --> 00:10:46,250
you've always been dedicated to the company.

164
00:10:46,280 --> 00:10:47,360
Why is Mr. Li looking for someone

165
00:10:47,360 --> 00:10:48,490
to share your power?

166
00:10:51,360 --> 00:10:52,680
That old fox, Li Qun,

167
00:10:52,680 --> 00:10:55,280
loves playing the game of checks and balances.

168
00:10:56,200 --> 00:10:58,800
How could he allow Shengshi to dominate alone?

169
00:11:00,400 --> 00:11:01,200
In the past,

170
00:11:01,640 --> 00:11:02,560
he used me

171
00:11:02,960 --> 00:11:04,000
to balance Ai Wei.

172
00:11:05,560 --> 00:11:07,240
Now it's my turn.

173
00:11:14,680 --> 00:11:16,080
What are your plans then?

174
00:11:43,400 --> 00:11:43,960
Old Lu,

175
00:11:44,760 --> 00:11:46,600
I've been waiting for your call.

176
00:11:47,280 --> 00:11:48,600
About what you told me before,

177
00:11:48,600 --> 00:11:49,400
is it okay?

178
00:11:50,120 --> 00:11:51,000
Of course.

179
00:11:51,560 --> 00:11:52,520
It's a

180
00:11:52,520 --> 00:11:55,400
legally operated eco-friendly material processing factory.

181
00:11:55,400 --> 00:11:57,600
We're not afraid of any investigation.

182
00:11:58,280 --> 00:11:59,080
You're right.

183
00:11:59,800 --> 00:12:01,320
A pie handed to you on a silver platter,

184
00:12:01,320 --> 00:12:02,650
why wouldn't you eat it?

185
00:12:03,640 --> 00:12:04,320
Exactly.

186
00:12:06,640 --> 00:12:07,500
How about this.

187
00:12:07,560 --> 00:12:08,960
Come to my place tonight.

188
00:12:09,160 --> 00:12:10,360
Let's talk in detail.

189
00:12:42,320 --> 00:12:42,850
Jin Tian.

190
00:12:47,960 --> 00:12:48,840
You scared me.

191
00:12:48,840 --> 00:12:49,920
Why are you here?

192
00:12:50,240 --> 00:12:51,720
You didn't answer my calls.

193
00:12:51,720 --> 00:12:53,000
You didn't reply to my messages.

194
00:12:53,000 --> 00:12:55,040
How long are you going to hide from me?

195
00:12:55,040 --> 00:12:55,840
Hide from you?

196
00:12:56,520 --> 00:12:57,780
Who's hiding from you?

197
00:12:58,600 --> 00:12:59,640
I was just too busy with work.

198
00:12:59,640 --> 00:13:01,170
I didn't have time to reply.

199
00:13:01,400 --> 00:13:01,800
Fine.

200
00:13:01,800 --> 00:13:02,680
You aren't hiding from me.

201
00:13:02,680 --> 00:13:04,940
Then come get a divorce with me right now.

202
00:13:05,040 --> 00:13:05,920
I told you.

203
00:13:05,920 --> 00:13:06,600
I'm extremely busy.

204
00:13:06,600 --> 00:13:07,320
I have a meeting this afternoon.

205
00:13:07,320 --> 00:13:08,000
I have a lot of things to do.

206
00:13:08,000 --> 00:13:09,280
Let's talk about it another day.

207
00:13:09,280 --> 00:13:11,320
What are you busy with?

208
00:13:11,640 --> 00:13:12,920
I asked your colleagues.

209
00:13:12,920 --> 00:13:15,380
You don't have any meetings this afternoon.

210
00:13:17,440 --> 00:13:19,080
I'm telling you, getting a divorce

211
00:13:19,080 --> 00:13:19,920
is a big deal.

212
00:13:19,920 --> 00:13:21,880
There are a lot of documents to prepare.

213
00:13:21,880 --> 00:13:23,200
I haven't prepared anything at all.

214
00:13:23,200 --> 00:13:24,880
So let's talk about it another day.

215
00:13:24,880 --> 00:13:25,440
No.

216
00:13:25,440 --> 00:13:26,970
What do you need to prepare?

217
00:13:27,240 --> 00:13:27,800
Marriage certificate,

218
00:13:27,800 --> 00:13:28,240
household register,

219
00:13:28,240 --> 00:13:28,720
ID card,

220
00:13:28,720 --> 00:13:29,760
and 2-inch photos.

221
00:13:29,760 --> 00:13:30,920
I've prepared everything that needs to be prepared.

222
00:13:30,920 --> 00:13:32,720
What else do you need to prepare?

223
00:13:33,240 --> 00:13:34,040
Lin Xiaoxiao,

224
00:13:35,160 --> 00:13:37,160
you've prepared quite thoroughly.

225
00:13:39,680 --> 00:13:41,960
I just don't want to waste our time.

226
00:13:42,400 --> 00:13:43,240
Waste time?

227
00:13:44,360 --> 00:13:45,560
I have plenty of time.

228
00:13:45,840 --> 00:13:46,560
Loads of it.

229
00:13:46,560 --> 00:13:47,160
I'm not in a hurry.

230
00:13:47,160 --> 00:13:48,080
Waste as much as you want.

231
00:13:48,080 --> 00:13:48,440
Let me tell you,

232
00:13:48,440 --> 00:13:49,570
this is just how I am.

233
00:13:49,600 --> 00:13:50,560
The more you force me to do something,

234
00:13:50,560 --> 00:13:51,820
the less I want to do it.

235
00:13:51,920 --> 00:13:53,920
Tie me up and drag me there if you can.

236
00:13:54,800 --> 00:13:55,480
Don't go.

237
00:13:55,480 --> 00:13:55,880
Stop pulling me.

238
00:13:55,880 --> 00:13:56,680
So many people are watching.

239
00:13:56,680 --> 00:13:58,120
What kind of man are you?

240
00:13:58,720 --> 00:13:59,560
Dragging it out like this,

241
00:13:59,560 --> 00:14:00,560
what's the point?

242
00:14:01,200 --> 00:14:01,840
I'm telling you,

243
00:14:01,840 --> 00:14:03,160
even if you keep dragging this out,

244
00:14:03,160 --> 00:14:04,560
I will still divorce you.

245
00:14:14,600 --> 00:14:15,400
Lin Xiaoxiao.

246
00:14:19,000 --> 00:14:22,000
Do you remember how many years we've known each other?

247
00:14:23,200 --> 00:14:24,600
A full ten years.

248
00:14:27,120 --> 00:14:28,000
You've only known that guy

249
00:14:28,000 --> 00:14:29,440
for a few months.

250
00:14:30,960 --> 00:14:32,160
Are you in such a hurry

251
00:14:32,160 --> 00:14:33,200
to cut ties with me

252
00:14:33,200 --> 00:14:35,060
and throw yourself into his arms?

253
00:14:37,000 --> 00:14:37,800
Is that it?

254
00:14:46,280 --> 00:14:48,560
Ending it soon is good for both of us.

255
00:14:57,960 --> 00:14:59,280
I will divorce you.

256
00:15:01,480 --> 00:15:03,340
But let me tell you, Lin Xiaoxiao,

257
00:15:03,800 --> 00:15:05,330
you'd better not regret it.

258
00:15:51,080 --> 00:15:51,640
Lili,

259
00:15:53,000 --> 00:15:53,520
look,

260
00:15:53,720 --> 00:15:55,560
the dumpling wrappers and the filling together

261
00:15:55,560 --> 00:15:57,360
only cost twenty or thirty yuan.

262
00:15:57,880 --> 00:15:59,720
If we make them and freeze them,

263
00:16:00,200 --> 00:16:01,860
they'll last you half a month.

264
00:16:03,520 --> 00:16:04,920
The meat we buy ourselves

265
00:16:05,160 --> 00:16:06,680
is hygienic and healthy,

266
00:16:07,320 --> 00:16:09,320
much better than ordering takeout.

267
00:16:10,120 --> 00:16:10,720
Yeah.

268
00:16:12,040 --> 00:16:13,900
This filling smells really good.

269
00:16:16,280 --> 00:16:18,120
These are Luo Xin's favorite.

270
00:16:23,560 --> 00:16:24,000
Lili,

271
00:16:24,440 --> 00:16:26,240
what kind of filling do you like?

272
00:16:27,440 --> 00:16:28,360
I love meat,

273
00:16:29,400 --> 00:16:30,800
any meat filling is fine.

274
00:16:31,160 --> 00:16:32,600
You can't just eat meat.

275
00:16:32,680 --> 00:16:34,080
You need a balanced diet.

276
00:16:36,040 --> 00:16:36,880
You know,

277
00:16:36,960 --> 00:16:38,920
when Luo Xin was little, he was a very picky eater.

278
00:16:38,920 --> 00:16:40,520
He wouldn't eat this or that,

279
00:16:41,280 --> 00:16:42,800
and was much shorter than his peers.

280
00:16:42,800 --> 00:16:44,200
I was so worried.

281
00:16:45,440 --> 00:16:47,480
Later, we had a neighbor from the Northeast

282
00:16:47,480 --> 00:16:49,410
who made dumplings every so often.

283
00:16:49,440 --> 00:16:51,300
They would make hundreds at a time

284
00:16:51,560 --> 00:16:53,490
and give them to all the neighbors.

285
00:16:54,240 --> 00:16:55,100
To my surprise,

286
00:16:55,480 --> 00:16:57,000
Luo Xin loved them.

287
00:16:58,360 --> 00:17:00,280
So I went to learn from them.

288
00:17:00,800 --> 00:17:02,280
I then took all the things Luo Xin wouldn't eat

289
00:17:02,280 --> 00:17:03,840
and put them inside the dumplings

290
00:17:03,840 --> 00:17:05,440
to coax him into eating them.

291
00:17:05,560 --> 00:17:06,480
Gradually,

292
00:17:06,480 --> 00:17:08,210
he started eating everything.

293
00:17:10,760 --> 00:17:13,160
Luo Xin is so lucky

294
00:17:13,480 --> 00:17:15,140
to have a good mother like you.

295
00:17:16,319 --> 00:17:18,200
All parents are the same.

296
00:17:18,920 --> 00:17:20,920
As long as their children need them,

297
00:17:21,040 --> 00:17:23,839
they would take their hearts out to make a filling.

298
00:17:24,480 --> 00:17:26,480
Isn't your mother like this?

299
00:17:35,880 --> 00:17:36,560
Yes.

300
00:17:42,440 --> 00:17:43,370
By the way, Lili,

301
00:17:44,400 --> 00:17:45,530
I've been in Beijing

302
00:17:47,200 --> 00:17:48,460
for more than ten days.

303
00:17:49,640 --> 00:17:51,320
Seeing that Luo Xin is doing well with you

304
00:17:51,320 --> 00:17:52,760
gives me peace of mind.

305
00:17:54,920 --> 00:17:56,200
I think I'll go back

306
00:17:57,040 --> 00:17:58,040
in a few days.

307
00:17:59,960 --> 00:18:02,420
People always have to return to their roots.

308
00:18:02,800 --> 00:18:04,000
My final days,

309
00:18:04,680 --> 00:18:06,610
I want to spend them in my hometown.

310
00:18:17,360 --> 00:18:18,120
Auntie,

311
00:18:20,640 --> 00:18:21,560
I think

312
00:18:24,840 --> 00:18:26,000
you still need to tell Luo Xin

313
00:18:26,000 --> 00:18:27,360
about your illness.

314
00:18:30,320 --> 00:18:32,320
You can't hide it like this forever.

315
00:18:35,120 --> 00:18:36,360
If he's the last one to know,

316
00:18:36,360 --> 00:18:37,920
he will be heartbroken.

317
00:18:42,200 --> 00:18:42,880
If I tell him now,

318
00:18:42,880 --> 00:18:44,680
wouldn't he be heartbroken too?

319
00:18:46,600 --> 00:18:48,760
Our whole family crying together

320
00:18:49,680 --> 00:18:50,840
is unnecessary.

321
00:18:51,280 --> 00:18:51,760
Auntie,

322
00:18:52,080 --> 00:18:52,400
All right,

323
00:18:52,400 --> 00:18:53,280
say no more.

324
00:18:56,720 --> 00:18:58,450
I made up my mind a long time ago.

325
00:19:02,720 --> 00:19:03,980
I just want to be alone,

326
00:19:05,760 --> 00:19:06,920
leaving cleanly

327
00:19:06,920 --> 00:19:08,120
and neatly.

328
00:19:10,280 --> 00:19:12,210
I want to leave this world quietly.

329
00:19:12,840 --> 00:19:14,200
I don't want to trouble my son.

330
00:19:14,200 --> 00:19:15,660
I don't want to be a burden.

331
00:19:18,000 --> 00:19:19,320
This is my last wish.

332
00:19:27,760 --> 00:19:28,760
Silly girl.

333
00:19:30,440 --> 00:19:31,400
He's back.

334
00:19:31,400 --> 00:19:32,200
Stop crying.

335
00:19:32,200 --> 00:19:33,080
Dry your tears.

336
00:19:38,800 --> 00:19:39,280
Lili.

337
00:19:39,680 --> 00:19:40,280
I'm back.

338
00:19:40,360 --> 00:19:41,090
You're back.

339
00:19:41,840 --> 00:19:43,840
Why did you come back so early today?

340
00:19:44,200 --> 00:19:45,880
There was nothing much at the company today.

341
00:19:45,880 --> 00:19:46,720
I got a leave slip,

342
00:19:46,720 --> 00:19:47,600
and snuck out.

343
00:19:52,120 --> 00:19:53,980
What a big setup you two have here.

344
00:19:54,080 --> 00:19:55,680
Mom, I'm in for a treat today.

345
00:19:55,680 --> 00:19:57,760
Your mom made your favorite,

346
00:19:57,760 --> 00:20:00,000
pork and zucchini.

347
00:20:00,840 --> 00:20:01,840
It smells so good.

348
00:20:03,920 --> 00:20:05,040
Don't just eat.

349
00:20:05,240 --> 00:20:07,100
You need to learn how to make some.

350
00:20:08,560 --> 00:20:09,400
I'll go wash my hands.

351
00:20:09,400 --> 00:20:10,400
I'll learn from you today

352
00:20:10,400 --> 00:20:11,400
about your craft.

353
00:20:17,600 --> 00:20:18,040
Lili.

354
00:20:18,920 --> 00:20:20,450
I see you're out of vinegar.

355
00:20:20,720 --> 00:20:22,650
I'll go downstairs to buy a bottle.

356
00:20:23,160 --> 00:20:23,520
No need.

357
00:20:23,520 --> 00:20:24,200
I'll go.

358
00:20:24,680 --> 00:20:25,080
No need.

359
00:20:25,080 --> 00:20:27,040
You don't even know which brand is good.

360
00:20:27,040 --> 00:20:27,840
Auntie, here.

361
00:20:28,480 --> 00:20:29,080
Take this.

362
00:20:30,480 --> 00:20:30,880
Luo Xin.

363
00:20:30,880 --> 00:20:33,210
I'm going downstairs to buy some vinegar.

364
00:20:33,800 --> 00:20:34,880
Stay safe, Mom.

365
00:20:39,120 --> 00:20:39,400
I really...

366
00:20:39,400 --> 00:20:41,330
I've never made dumplings before.

367
00:20:41,960 --> 00:20:43,120
How do you do this?

368
00:20:44,160 --> 00:20:45,440
Just put the filling in the middle.

369
00:20:45,440 --> 00:20:46,900
Use a little, not too much.

370
00:20:47,720 --> 00:20:48,560
Is this okay?

371
00:20:50,800 --> 00:20:51,160
Baby.

372
00:20:52,320 --> 00:20:53,850
I have to ask you something.

373
00:20:54,960 --> 00:20:56,080
A few days ago,

374
00:20:56,080 --> 00:20:57,680
didn't you go out with my mom?

375
00:21:00,000 --> 00:21:01,400
Do you feel like

376
00:21:02,400 --> 00:21:04,200
she's been acting weird lately?

377
00:21:08,720 --> 00:21:10,480
I think she's fine.

378
00:21:10,480 --> 00:21:11,560
She had a lot of fun.

379
00:21:12,760 --> 00:21:14,520
I know my mom.

380
00:21:14,520 --> 00:21:15,880
She's straightforward,

381
00:21:15,880 --> 00:21:17,410
and she can't keep a secret.

382
00:21:18,880 --> 00:21:20,200
But this time,

383
00:21:22,160 --> 00:21:23,360
I feel like she's hiding something from me.

384
00:21:23,360 --> 00:21:24,040
It's weird.

385
00:21:26,360 --> 00:21:28,290
You're definitely overthinking.

386
00:21:32,120 --> 00:21:33,200
Here, let me help you.

387
00:21:33,200 --> 00:21:34,330
What are you making?

388
00:21:34,640 --> 00:21:35,240
Like this.

389
00:21:35,760 --> 00:21:36,690
Let me teach you.

390
00:21:37,280 --> 00:21:38,340
Take some filling.

391
00:21:38,920 --> 00:21:40,380
Let me get some for you too.

392
00:21:41,120 --> 00:21:41,480
Okay.

393
00:21:44,280 --> 00:21:46,360
Making dumplings isn't that simple.

394
00:21:48,840 --> 00:21:49,760
There are so many steps.

395
00:21:49,760 --> 00:21:50,520
Yeah.

396
00:21:51,280 --> 00:21:54,480
Your mom has been making dumplings for you for so many years.

397
00:21:54,480 --> 00:21:55,240
It's not easy for her.

398
00:21:55,240 --> 00:21:55,720
Here.

399
00:21:55,920 --> 00:21:56,840
Fold it in half.

400
00:21:58,200 --> 00:21:59,200
Fold it like this.

401
00:22:00,000 --> 00:22:00,600
Fold halfway,

402
00:22:00,600 --> 00:22:01,600
and fold again.

403
00:22:01,600 --> 00:22:02,040
Right.

404
00:22:02,800 --> 00:22:04,640
Then squeeze this again.

405
00:22:48,040 --> 00:22:48,480
Ma'am,

406
00:22:49,160 --> 00:22:49,600
Ma'am,

407
00:22:49,760 --> 00:22:50,680
are you okay?

408
00:23:02,040 --> 00:23:02,640
Slow down.

409
00:23:03,640 --> 00:23:06,900
Why hasn't Mrs. Wang come back after going down for so long?

410
00:23:06,920 --> 00:23:07,650
I don't know.

411
00:23:11,840 --> 00:23:13,480
How about I go down and check?

412
00:23:13,880 --> 00:23:14,360
Don't.

413
00:23:14,360 --> 00:23:15,080
I'll go.

414
00:23:16,320 --> 00:23:17,680
Just wipe this table.

415
00:23:25,440 --> 00:23:25,920
My mom.

416
00:23:26,760 --> 00:23:27,420
Hello, Mom.

417
00:23:30,680 --> 00:23:31,200
What?

418
00:24:03,240 --> 00:24:04,000
The patient's liver cancer

419
00:24:04,000 --> 00:24:05,560
has advanced to the intermediate stage.

420
00:24:05,560 --> 00:24:07,760
Considering the patient's condition,

421
00:24:07,840 --> 00:24:09,720
before the cancer cells spread,

422
00:24:09,880 --> 00:24:12,840
it's best to perform a liver transplant as soon as possible.

423
00:24:12,840 --> 00:24:14,640
Any later and it will be too late.

424
00:24:15,000 --> 00:24:16,680
And right now, we

425
00:24:16,680 --> 00:24:18,360
can't guarantee

426
00:24:18,480 --> 00:24:21,000
that she'll be completely fine after the transplant.

427
00:24:21,000 --> 00:24:22,920
It all depends on the patient's condition

428
00:24:22,920 --> 00:24:24,200
after the surgery.

429
00:24:24,960 --> 00:24:25,840
After surgery, some people

430
00:24:25,840 --> 00:24:27,200
can live for six months to a year.

431
00:24:27,200 --> 00:24:28,280
But others

432
00:24:28,400 --> 00:24:30,000
can live for ten, twenty,

433
00:24:30,000 --> 00:24:31,440
or even more years.

434
00:24:32,200 --> 00:24:32,920
So,

435
00:24:33,320 --> 00:24:35,180
you need to be mentally prepared.

436
00:24:56,720 --> 00:24:57,800
I'm sorry.

437
00:25:01,000 --> 00:25:02,930
Your mom told me to keep it from you.

438
00:25:06,560 --> 00:25:07,880
She was so firm.

439
00:25:08,680 --> 00:25:10,680
I really couldn't talk her out of it.

440
00:25:14,720 --> 00:25:15,320
It's fine.

441
00:25:16,520 --> 00:25:17,520
I don't blame you.

442
00:25:20,400 --> 00:25:21,730
My mom is just like that.

443
00:27:23,080 --> 00:27:24,880
I used to think this kind of thing

444
00:27:27,960 --> 00:27:29,490
was pretty far away from me.

445
00:27:36,840 --> 00:27:39,300
I never thought it would happen to me one day.

446
00:27:52,760 --> 00:27:53,840
Have I ever told you

447
00:27:56,320 --> 00:27:59,380
that my family ran a small grocery store when I was a kid?

448
00:28:06,560 --> 00:28:07,800
Our store

449
00:28:10,920 --> 00:28:13,450
wasn't the most profitable one on the street,

450
00:28:16,560 --> 00:28:17,960
but it was the liveliest.

451
00:28:20,760 --> 00:28:22,690
From morning till night every day,

452
00:28:23,560 --> 00:28:26,490
there were always aunties sitting around chatting.

453
00:28:28,280 --> 00:28:30,540
My mom stuck all my certificates of merit

454
00:28:30,600 --> 00:28:31,640
on the wall.

455
00:28:34,480 --> 00:28:36,410
She would brag to everyone she met,

456
00:28:38,080 --> 00:28:39,000
'Look at my son.

457
00:28:40,400 --> 00:28:41,840
He got this rank again.

458
00:28:42,840 --> 00:28:45,440
And his teacher praised him for this and that.'

459
00:28:49,080 --> 00:28:51,360
She didn't care if others wanted to hear it

460
00:28:51,360 --> 00:28:53,290
or how many times they had heard it.

461
00:28:57,040 --> 00:28:58,040
So for a while,

462
00:28:58,040 --> 00:29:00,170
I became the 'kid from another family'

463
00:29:01,280 --> 00:29:02,680
in the eyes of all the children

464
00:29:02,680 --> 00:29:03,800
on that street.

465
00:29:07,800 --> 00:29:10,130
I couldn't even find a friend to play with.

466
00:29:17,760 --> 00:29:19,000
Actually, growing up,

467
00:29:19,000 --> 00:29:20,760
I was always my parents' pride.

468
00:29:27,000 --> 00:29:27,800
No matter what I did,

469
00:29:27,800 --> 00:29:28,860
they supported me.

470
00:29:30,840 --> 00:29:32,370
When I applied for college,

471
00:29:34,200 --> 00:29:36,860
I filled out the application form all by myself.

472
00:29:38,680 --> 00:29:40,340
I was so proud when I came back.

473
00:29:41,440 --> 00:29:42,240
I said,

474
00:29:43,640 --> 00:29:45,440
'I'm not here for your opinions.

475
00:29:46,800 --> 00:29:48,680
I'm here to tell you my decision.'

476
00:29:54,800 --> 00:29:56,060
My mom just smiled at me

477
00:30:01,840 --> 00:30:02,700
and said, 'Son,

478
00:30:05,240 --> 00:30:06,500
as long as you like it.'

479
00:30:22,800 --> 00:30:24,660
Her supporting what you like to do

480
00:30:26,640 --> 00:30:28,970
is their way of showing their love for you.

481
00:30:36,240 --> 00:30:37,640
Now that I think about it,

482
00:30:40,560 --> 00:30:41,600
growing up,

483
00:30:44,520 --> 00:30:45,240
getting into college,

484
00:30:45,240 --> 00:30:46,040
finding a job,

485
00:30:47,440 --> 00:30:48,920
I was really willful.

486
00:30:54,080 --> 00:30:54,880
But today,

487
00:30:56,600 --> 00:30:57,680
before today,

488
00:31:02,400 --> 00:31:04,400
I was still proud of my willfulness.

489
00:31:09,240 --> 00:31:10,440
Look how awesome I am.

490
00:31:11,760 --> 00:31:12,960
I have such pursuits.

491
00:31:15,120 --> 00:31:16,400
I don't bow to capital.

492
00:31:17,960 --> 00:31:19,620
I don't compromise with life.

493
00:31:24,760 --> 00:31:26,400
But today I realized

494
00:31:29,200 --> 00:31:30,840
why I could be willful.

495
00:31:34,520 --> 00:31:35,760
It's because my parents

496
00:31:35,760 --> 00:31:37,840
didn't make any demands of me.

497
00:31:41,880 --> 00:31:43,400
They did everything

498
00:31:43,400 --> 00:31:44,600
they possibly could.

499
00:31:46,200 --> 00:31:48,440
But I've never done anything for them.

500
00:32:01,000 --> 00:32:02,720
How am I their pride?

501
00:32:05,920 --> 00:32:06,960
What can I do?

502
00:32:09,400 --> 00:32:10,530
What am I capable of?

503
00:32:11,760 --> 00:32:12,760
I'm thirty years old,

504
00:32:12,760 --> 00:32:14,560
and I've accomplished nothing.

505
00:32:17,320 --> 00:32:18,600
My mom got sick,

506
00:32:18,600 --> 00:32:20,400
and I can't do anything about it.

507
00:32:38,640 --> 00:32:39,920
It's okay, Luo Xin.

508
00:32:47,680 --> 00:32:49,160
I'll face it with you.

509
00:32:55,400 --> 00:32:56,040
It's fine.

510
00:32:57,000 --> 00:32:57,760
It will pass.

511
00:33:35,560 --> 00:33:36,220
From now on,

512
00:33:36,320 --> 00:33:37,580
I'll be relying on you.

513
00:33:38,240 --> 00:33:39,400
Call me if you need anything.

514
00:33:39,400 --> 00:33:39,960
Okay.

515
00:33:42,680 --> 00:33:44,000
You're back.

516
00:33:44,200 --> 00:33:44,640
Hello.

517
00:33:45,760 --> 00:33:47,560
I'll leave you to your business.

518
00:33:47,840 --> 00:33:48,240
Bye.

519
00:33:48,440 --> 00:33:48,970
Goodbye.

520
00:33:52,720 --> 00:33:54,360
Were you two talking about something?

521
00:33:54,360 --> 00:33:55,200
Didn't I tell you

522
00:33:55,200 --> 00:33:56,360
not to come here unless it's urgent?

523
00:33:56,360 --> 00:33:57,760
What if someone sees you?

524
00:33:57,920 --> 00:33:59,120
And didn't I tell you

525
00:33:59,120 --> 00:34:01,320
that I have something very important to say?

526
00:34:01,320 --> 00:34:03,120
Guess what I did this afternoon.

527
00:34:08,800 --> 00:34:10,280
I went to file for divorce.

528
00:34:11,040 --> 00:34:12,320
In thirty days,

529
00:34:12,320 --> 00:34:13,520
I will be a free woman.

530
00:34:14,199 --> 00:34:15,199
And the two of us

531
00:34:15,199 --> 00:34:17,080
can finally be together openly.

532
00:34:25,040 --> 00:34:25,600
What?

533
00:34:25,600 --> 00:34:26,840
Aren't you happy?

534
00:34:28,880 --> 00:34:29,520
I am.

535
00:34:30,280 --> 00:34:32,239
You made a choice for yourself,

536
00:34:32,440 --> 00:34:33,969
of course I'm happy for you.

537
00:35:01,760 --> 00:35:03,280
I told you I won't have the surgery,

538
00:35:03,280 --> 00:35:04,480
and I mean it.

539
00:35:04,800 --> 00:35:06,130
Why are you so stubborn?

540
00:35:07,240 --> 00:35:08,320
What's going on?

541
00:35:08,840 --> 00:35:10,040
Lili, you're just in time.

542
00:35:10,040 --> 00:35:11,170
Help me talk him into

543
00:35:11,400 --> 00:35:13,330
getting me discharged right away.

544
00:35:13,400 --> 00:35:14,440
Sleeping here

545
00:35:14,440 --> 00:35:16,200
makes my whole body ache.

546
00:35:16,560 --> 00:35:17,360
No, Auntie.

547
00:35:17,360 --> 00:35:19,080
You really have to listen to Luo Xin.

548
00:35:19,080 --> 00:35:20,000
The doctor also said

549
00:35:20,000 --> 00:35:21,640
surgery is the best option.

550
00:35:21,880 --> 00:35:23,200
As long as we find a suitable liver donor.

551
00:35:23,200 --> 00:35:25,000
I know about liver transplants.

552
00:35:27,440 --> 00:35:29,080
We'll spend all our savings,

553
00:35:29,960 --> 00:35:31,720
and I might only live for another year or so.

554
00:35:31,720 --> 00:35:32,120
Mom,

555
00:35:32,120 --> 00:35:33,480
the doctor said

556
00:35:34,280 --> 00:35:35,360
with proper care after the surgery,

557
00:35:35,360 --> 00:35:37,520
60% of people can live for over ten years.

558
00:35:37,520 --> 00:35:39,080
What if I'm in the other 40%?

559
00:35:41,120 --> 00:35:42,040
The money is gone,

560
00:35:42,040 --> 00:35:42,600
and my life is gone.

561
00:35:42,600 --> 00:35:43,860
It's just not worth it.

562
00:35:44,040 --> 00:35:45,440
And I suffer for nothing.

563
00:35:45,720 --> 00:35:46,320
Can you please

564
00:35:46,320 --> 00:35:48,250
stop worrying about money for now?

565
00:35:48,360 --> 00:35:49,960
You just need to cooperate with the treatment.

566
00:35:49,960 --> 00:35:50,720
Okay?

567
00:35:51,160 --> 00:35:52,520
If we don't have enough money,

568
00:35:52,520 --> 00:35:54,580
I'll sell the house in Yanjiao, okay?

569
00:35:55,680 --> 00:35:56,610
What did you say?

570
00:35:58,800 --> 00:36:00,640
You want to sell the house?

571
00:36:02,320 --> 00:36:03,720
You're 30 years old.

572
00:36:03,720 --> 00:36:05,240
You finally settled down in Beijing.

573
00:36:05,240 --> 00:36:06,440
If you sell the house,

574
00:36:06,440 --> 00:36:08,120
how will you get married?

575
00:36:09,840 --> 00:36:11,800
I didn't want this to happen.

576
00:36:11,800 --> 00:36:13,200
That's why I didn't want to tell you.

577
00:36:13,200 --> 00:36:14,400
If you do this,

578
00:36:14,960 --> 00:36:16,690
I won't be able to rest in peace.

579
00:36:16,960 --> 00:36:18,040
Don't be like this.

580
00:36:18,040 --> 00:36:18,970
I'm telling you,

581
00:36:19,160 --> 00:36:20,480
it's my life.

582
00:36:20,960 --> 00:36:23,090
I decide whether to get treated or not.

583
00:36:23,160 --> 00:36:24,840
Even if you tie me to the operating table,

584
00:36:24,840 --> 00:36:26,560
I still won't have the surgery.

585
00:36:26,560 --> 00:36:27,000
Mom.

586
00:36:27,000 --> 00:36:27,600
All right,

587
00:36:27,600 --> 00:36:28,480
stop arguing.

588
00:36:29,480 --> 00:36:31,210
Luo Xin, wait outside for a bit.

589
00:36:31,480 --> 00:36:33,010
Let me talk to Auntie alone.

590
00:36:46,640 --> 00:36:47,280
Auntie.

591
00:36:47,280 --> 00:36:48,120
Lili,

592
00:36:50,600 --> 00:36:52,000
don't try to persuade me.

593
00:36:54,600 --> 00:36:56,000
Once I've made up my mind,

594
00:36:56,840 --> 00:36:58,040
no one can change it.

595
00:37:06,400 --> 00:37:07,040
Auntie.

596
00:37:08,120 --> 00:37:10,040
Do you remember when you asked me

597
00:37:12,040 --> 00:37:13,360
how my mom treated me?

598
00:37:17,880 --> 00:37:19,610
I didn't answer you right away.

599
00:37:21,400 --> 00:37:22,160
Actually,

600
00:37:25,600 --> 00:37:27,000
I don't really remember.

601
00:37:33,560 --> 00:37:35,840
My mom died of illness when I was five.

602
00:37:47,120 --> 00:37:48,600
I was too young back then,

603
00:37:49,480 --> 00:37:51,610
so I didn't understand a lot of things.

604
00:37:53,160 --> 00:37:54,120
I just remember,

605
00:37:55,360 --> 00:37:56,520
during that time,

606
00:37:57,280 --> 00:38:00,480
she always wore a blue-and-white striped hospital gown.

607
00:38:01,400 --> 00:38:04,040
She always smelled like disinfectant.

608
00:38:05,880 --> 00:38:07,760
Every day at a certain time,

609
00:38:08,840 --> 00:38:10,770
she would feel very uncomfortable

610
00:38:11,000 --> 00:38:12,060
and in a lot of pain.

611
00:38:13,720 --> 00:38:14,450
Where's Dad?

612
00:38:15,080 --> 00:38:17,000
Dad went to buy breakfast.

613
00:38:17,280 --> 00:38:19,160
Dad said you are in a lot of pain.

614
00:38:19,160 --> 00:38:20,200
Are you?

615
00:38:22,960 --> 00:38:24,000
Lili,

616
00:38:25,080 --> 00:38:26,400
Mom is not in pain.

617
00:38:27,120 --> 00:38:28,520
Really?

618
00:38:29,880 --> 00:38:32,040
When has Mom ever lied to you?

619
00:38:40,520 --> 00:38:41,320
Lili,

620
00:38:42,320 --> 00:38:43,880
go play by the door for a while.

621
00:38:43,880 --> 00:38:44,960
Don't go too far.

622
00:38:45,840 --> 00:38:47,160
Got it, Mom.

623
00:38:48,640 --> 00:38:49,600
Good girl.

624
00:38:49,960 --> 00:38:50,880
Go ahead.

625
00:39:24,240 --> 00:39:24,840
Later on,

626
00:39:28,600 --> 00:39:30,000
I dreamt of that scene

627
00:39:30,000 --> 00:39:31,960
countless times in my dreams.

628
00:39:35,280 --> 00:39:36,760
I really regret it.

629
00:39:39,120 --> 00:39:41,480
I really wished my mom, even just once,

630
00:39:43,160 --> 00:39:44,520
would tell me the truth.

631
00:39:46,840 --> 00:39:48,440
I wished she could tell me

632
00:39:48,840 --> 00:39:50,900
that she was actually in a lot of pain.

633
00:39:51,880 --> 00:39:54,000
That she wanted me to stay with her.

634
00:39:59,960 --> 00:40:01,690
Even though I couldn't do much,

635
00:40:03,920 --> 00:40:06,160
at least I would feel a lot better.

636
00:40:13,840 --> 00:40:14,400
Auntie,

637
00:40:17,720 --> 00:40:20,200
you parents are all used to this.

638
00:40:24,400 --> 00:40:27,330
Always thinking about your children in everything,

639
00:40:27,840 --> 00:40:29,600
never considering yourselves,

640
00:40:29,600 --> 00:40:31,280
and just blindly giving.

641
00:40:33,720 --> 00:40:34,580
You always say,

642
00:40:35,360 --> 00:40:36,360
I'm not in pain,

643
00:40:37,080 --> 00:40:38,000
I'm fine,

644
00:40:39,560 --> 00:40:40,960
and I'm doing well.

645
00:40:46,640 --> 00:40:47,760
If you really

646
00:40:48,320 --> 00:40:50,050
want to think of your children,

647
00:40:50,160 --> 00:40:52,620
you must first take good care of yourselves.

648
00:40:58,240 --> 00:40:58,960
Back then,

649
00:41:00,280 --> 00:41:02,810
I didn't get to spend quality time with my mom.

650
00:41:06,360 --> 00:41:08,840
It became the biggest regret of my life.

651
00:41:14,200 --> 00:41:16,000
I think it's the same for Luo Xin.

652
00:41:30,320 --> 00:41:31,120
Lili,

653
00:41:35,160 --> 00:41:36,120
I understand.

654
00:42:04,120 --> 00:42:04,640
Mr. Luo,

655
00:42:05,040 --> 00:42:06,840
this house of yours doesn't have a property ownership certificate,

656
00:42:06,840 --> 00:42:08,160
so the title cannot be transferred.

657
00:42:08,160 --> 00:42:09,760
Ms. Wang, I really know that.

658
00:42:09,760 --> 00:42:10,480
But in a few months,

659
00:42:10,480 --> 00:42:12,560
my property certificate will be issued.

660
00:42:12,560 --> 00:42:13,560
Please help me think of another way.

661
00:42:13,560 --> 00:42:15,020
I need the money urgently.

662
00:42:16,560 --> 00:42:17,600
If you

663
00:42:18,000 --> 00:42:20,240
really need capital turnover urgently,

664
00:42:20,240 --> 00:42:21,200
I actually

665
00:42:21,480 --> 00:42:22,610
could give you a tip.

666
00:42:23,160 --> 00:42:24,090
Tell me quickly.

667
00:42:25,200 --> 00:42:26,120
The state now

668
00:42:26,240 --> 00:42:29,000
provides great support for small and micro businesses.

669
00:42:29,000 --> 00:42:30,640
Relevant taxes and fees are completely exempted.

670
00:42:30,640 --> 00:42:32,320
And there are interest-free loans.

671
00:42:32,320 --> 00:42:33,960
You can register a company,

672
00:42:34,200 --> 00:42:36,000
create a good-looking cash flow,

673
00:42:36,000 --> 00:42:36,680
and then

674
00:42:36,680 --> 00:42:38,600
you can use the company's name

675
00:42:38,600 --> 00:42:39,680
to get a bank loan.

676
00:42:41,000 --> 00:42:43,000
Isn't this just registering a shell company

677
00:42:43,000 --> 00:42:44,800
to exploit a loophole in the law?

678
00:42:45,680 --> 00:42:46,920
Rules are dead,

679
00:42:47,120 --> 00:42:48,320
but people are alive.

680
00:42:48,560 --> 00:42:49,320
Previously,

681
00:42:49,360 --> 00:42:50,640
a client of our company

682
00:42:50,640 --> 00:42:52,120
wanted to take out a loan to buy a house.

683
00:42:52,120 --> 00:42:53,400
The mortgage was rejected,

684
00:42:53,400 --> 00:42:55,060
so they used this exact trick.

685
00:42:55,800 --> 00:42:56,960
I have a relative

686
00:42:56,960 --> 00:42:59,240
who specializes in helping people do this.

687
00:42:59,240 --> 00:43:01,560
He can help you get all the documents ready.

688
00:43:01,560 --> 00:43:03,240
The bank won't be able to tell.

689
00:43:04,080 --> 00:43:06,240
It's not like we are taking out a malicious loan.

690
00:43:06,240 --> 00:43:08,280
Once your house is sold,

691
00:43:08,280 --> 00:43:10,080
you can pay the money back to the bank.

692
00:43:10,080 --> 00:43:11,010
Isn't that fine?

693
00:43:12,440 --> 00:43:13,240
This won't do.

694
00:43:14,360 --> 00:43:15,280
We're not doing this.

695
00:43:15,280 --> 00:43:16,080
I'm sorry.

696
00:43:20,240 --> 00:43:21,570
Luo Xin, let me tell you.

697
00:43:22,000 --> 00:43:23,120
This is forging documents

698
00:43:23,120 --> 00:43:23,880
and defrauding loans.

699
00:43:23,880 --> 00:43:24,960
We really can't do this.

700
00:43:24,960 --> 00:43:26,160
But once there's a suitable liver source,

701
00:43:26,160 --> 00:43:27,760
my mom will have to undergo surgery.

702
00:43:27,760 --> 00:43:29,020
This can't be delayed.

703
00:43:29,960 --> 00:43:30,840
And in such a short time,

704
00:43:30,840 --> 00:43:33,170
where am I supposed to get that much money?

705
00:43:35,280 --> 00:43:35,960
This won't work.

706
00:43:35,960 --> 00:43:37,420
Don't even think about it.

707
00:45:39,120 --> 00:45:39,800
Mr. Lu,

708
00:45:39,800 --> 00:45:41,400
will you be at the office tomorrow?

709
00:45:41,400 --> 00:45:42,530
I want to talk to you.

710
00:45:57,680 --> 00:45:57,840
Jiangzi.
